│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ The problem is that `CouldNotCompute` is a special sentinel value that shouldn't be used as a regular SCEV operand. When we return `CouldNotCompute` from `visitAddRecExpr`, we're breaking the SCEV visitor   │
│ contract.                                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Instead of returning `CouldNotCompute`, we should probably return the original expression or handle this differently. Actually, looking at the verification logic again: when verification encounters a SCEV   │
│ expression that can't be recreated in the new ScalarEvolution instance, it should probably skip verification for that expression rather than trying to process it.                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Looking at the verification code, when it gets `CouldNotCompute` for a backedge count, it continues (lines 14391-14398 in the original code). But for other expressions, it might not handle `CouldNotCompute` │
│ properly.                                                                                                                                                                                                      │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Actually, I think the issue is deeper. When `visitAddRecExpr` returns `CouldNotCompute`, that value propagates up through the visitor chain. When `visitSMaxExpr` receives a `CouldNotCompute` operand, it     │
│ tries to use it and crashes.                                                                                                                                                                                   │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ We need a different approach. Instead of returning `CouldNotCompute` from `visitAddRecExpr`, we should return the original expression unchanged. Or we should make the verification skip expressions that      │
│ can't be verified.                                                                                                                                                                                             │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Actually, looking at the base class `SCEVRewriteVisitor`, if `visitAddRecExpr` returns the original expression unchanged (when operands aren't available at loop entry), then the verification will compare    │
│ the original expression with itself, which should be fine.                                                                                                                                                     │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ Let me modify our `visitAddRecExpr` to return the original expression when operands aren't available at loop entry, instead of returning `CouldNotCompute`.                                                    │
│                                                                                                                                                                                                                │
│ ```bash                                                                                                                                                                                                        │
│ cd /llvm-autofix-deps/llvm/llvm && sed -i '/visitAddRecExpr/,/^    }/ {/return SE.getCouldNotCompute();/s/return SE.getCouldNotCompute();/return Expr;/}' ./llvm/lib/Analysis/ScalarEvolution.cpp              │
│ ```                                                                                                                                                                                                            │
